Uses of Class
GrammarNotions.Context_Terms.CTerm

  • Packages that use CTerm 
    Package Description
    Boxes
    Provides classes for defining the various box operators used by formatter components for text formatting.
    GrammarNotions.Context_Terms
    Provides classes for defining context, terms, items of Signatures.
    GrammarNotions.Grammar
    Classes implementing the Structural representation of a grammar.
    GrammarNotions.RegExpr
    Classes defining the different kinds of regular expressions.
    GrammarNotions.SyntaxExpr
    Classes defining the different kinds of syntax expressions for concrete syntax.
    Signatures
    Provides classes implementing a signature.

    • Uses of CTerm in Boxes

      Subclasses of CTerm in Boxes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  CArgDataBox
      Creates a box operator used in patterns to distinguish data elements.
      class  CArgNodeBox
      Creates a box operator used in patterns to distinguish subtrees.
      class  CBox
      CBox is a base class which provides methods for creating the different kinds of box operators.
      class  CBox_List
      Resizable array implementation of a list of boxes.
      class  CFlowListBox
      A box operator which formats boxes horizontally until no more boxes fit on the same line (i.e., uses multiple lines).
      class  CHorBox
      A box operator for horizontal formatting of boxes.
      class  CHorSepListBox
      A box operator for horizontal formatting of boxes with a separator.
      class  CIndBox
      An indentation box operator.
      class  CSelBox
      Specifies a selectable box.
      class  CTermBox
      Formats a terminal symbol without data.
      class  CTermDataBox
      Formats a terminal symbol with data.
      class  CVerBox
      A box operator for vertical formatting of boxes.
      class  CVerSepListBox
      A box operator for vertical formatting of boxes with a separator.
